{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01P8vL7eGqbCZvwEXxPyiRyx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The paper compiles cleanly to a 12-page PDF at `paper_draft/main.pdf` with no LaTeX errors.\n\n**Deliverables at `paper_draft/`:**\n- `main.tex` — NeurIPS 2025 style with `[final,main]` options, hyperref, booktabs, all command imports\n- `commands/macros.tex` — Project-specific macros (`\\ours`, `\\parentmodel`, `\\glickformer`, etc.)\n- `sections/{abstract,introduction,related_work,methodology,results,discussion,conclusion}.tex` — Full prose, no placeholders\n- `references.bib` — 11 BibTeX entries (GlickFormer, ChessFormer, RatingNet, Maia/Maia-2, BigData Cup, Lichess, scikit-learn, python-chess, isotonic)\n- `figures/` — 4 PNGs copied from experiment (decile calibration, feature importance, pred-vs-actual, residuals)\n\n**Key content:**\n- Title emphasizes the novel contribution: *Tactical Density Features for CPU-Only Prediction of Lichess Puzzle Difficulty*\n- Abstract, intro, and results consistently report the headline numbers: MAE 240.8, Spearman 0.768, mid-decile cal 85.6, ΔMAE 0.12 across seeds\n- Controlled ablation vs 141-dim parent isolates the 14-feature tactical-density block as the sole source of the 12.8-Elo improvement\n- Contribution bullets use action verbs; tables use booktabs with bolded best in-family results; hyperref makes all references clickable\n- Two `\\renewcommand`s in `commands/general.tex` requiring `algpseudocode` were commented out (we don't use algorithms)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":344,"cache_read_input_tokens":107164,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":344},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6fbcd0a4-5ad7-4447-9fee-7a7864e1073f","uui